WEBVTT

00:00.012 --> 00:01.726
<i>Previously on</i>
Covert Affairs...

00:01.851 --> 00:03.592
Simon is a master spy.

00:03.692 --> 00:05.393
Get intimate enough
with a man,

00:05.461 --> 00:06.961
and he'll tell you everything.
I like you...

00:07.029 --> 00:08.663
Quite a bit more
than you might believe.

00:08.731 --> 00:12.367
Simon, it's me.
Can I see you?

00:12.434 --> 00:14.235
I'm on the short list, Joan,
to be the ambassador to China.

00:14.303 --> 00:16.070
The promise
of the Chinese ambassador post

00:16.138 --> 00:18.706
is pulling you away like you
no longer work here.

00:18.774 --> 00:20.975
The DCI has put me
on the trilateral commission

00:21.043 --> 00:22.210
looking into Jai's death.

00:22.278 --> 00:23.845
People think
I murdered my own son?

00:25.000 --> 00:31.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:37.725 --> 00:39.392
Hey.

00:41.897 --> 00:45.800
For a week trip,
you pack kind of light.

00:48.270 --> 00:49.609
Please tell me
you're not wearing this.

00:49.610 --> 00:51.677
I'm going on a business trip
to the Caribbean.

00:51.745 --> 00:53.179
Unless you're applying
for a job at Sandals,

00:53.246 --> 00:55.348
I would lose this shirt.

01:00.320 --> 01:03.623
What kind of business
do you have in the Caribbean?

01:03.690 --> 01:05.825
Oh, I have my finger
in a number of...

01:05.892 --> 01:09.161
Pies.
Pies. Yeah, I know.

01:09.229 --> 01:11.564
What kind of pies,
specifically?

01:11.632 --> 01:13.232
Apple, rhubarb...

01:13.300 --> 01:15.568
cherry,
when I'm in the mood.

01:15.636 --> 01:17.703
This is always the worst part.

01:17.771 --> 01:19.005
The fashion tips?

01:19.072 --> 01:20.306
The end.

01:20.374 --> 01:22.208
We're always saying good-bye,

01:22.275 --> 01:25.077
and we never know when we're
gonna see each other again.

01:28.982 --> 01:30.249
Come with me...

01:30.317 --> 01:31.350
on my trip--

01:31.418 --> 01:33.085
a week together in paradise.

01:33.153 --> 01:34.220
You have to work.

01:34.287 --> 01:36.355
I don't want to interfere.

01:36.423 --> 01:40.626
Well, I've never had a problem
mixing business and pleasure.

01:40.694 --> 01:43.262
Have you?

01:43.330 --> 01:46.432
I do have some vacation time
saved up and...

01:46.500 --> 01:49.350
a bikini I've been dying
to wear.

01:49.861 --> 01:53.364
Or not wear.

01:53.432 --> 01:56.333
Where are you going--
Bahamas, Caymans?

01:56.401 --> 01:58.769
Cuba.

01:58.837 --> 02:02.139
Still interested?

02:05.177 --> 02:07.611
When do we leave?

02:12.784 --> 02:14.318
Hey. Thanks for seeing me
before work.

02:14.386 --> 02:16.153
My door is always open.

02:16.221 --> 02:20.524
It doesn't matter which door.
Come on in.

02:20.592 --> 02:24.095
So you want to go on vacation
with a seasoned FSB operative

02:24.162 --> 02:26.897
who very well
may be on to you.

02:26.965 --> 02:28.999
Or he may be letting his
emotions guide his decisions.

02:29.067 --> 02:31.735
And he's taking you to Cuba?

02:31.803 --> 02:33.003
I know the risks.

02:33.071 --> 02:34.605
If I got caught,

02:34.673 --> 02:36.774
the extraction
would be extremely high risk.

02:36.842 --> 02:38.709
Extraction?

02:38.777 --> 02:40.077
There would be no extraction.

02:40.145 --> 02:44.248
If you got caught, the Agency
would have no recourse.

02:44.316 --> 02:45.850
North Korea would be easier.

02:45.917 --> 02:49.120
Still,
the potential benefit is huge.

02:49.187 --> 02:52.022
Are you asking me to authorize
a mission to Cuba?

02:52.090 --> 02:55.459
'Cause if you are,
I can't give you that.

02:55.527 --> 02:58.696
But if you're telling me
you're gonna go anyway,

02:58.763 --> 03:02.199
I can't stop you.

03:02.267 --> 03:05.035
I can't use
my regular passport.

03:05.103 --> 03:07.338
The Agency
would be able to track me.

03:07.405 --> 03:09.039
So I need an outside forgery.

03:09.107 --> 03:10.174
I know a guy.

03:10.242 --> 03:11.775
Simon saw my passport
in Morocco,

03:11.843 --> 03:14.311
so the stamps
would have to match exactly.

03:14.379 --> 03:16.480
A replacement will find its
way to you before your flight.

03:16.548 --> 03:18.949
Now, Simon will probably fly you
through Mexico.

03:19.017 --> 03:21.318
It's the easiest way
to get Americans into Cuba.

03:21.386 --> 03:22.820
Once I land,
there will be eyes on me.

03:22.888 --> 03:24.722
Cuba has always been
a hotbed of Russian spies.

03:24.789 --> 03:26.857
They'd love to catch
an outside player.

03:26.925 --> 03:28.726
So don't get caught.

03:28.793 --> 03:30.794
Spycraft wouldn't be that much
fun without the bad guys,

03:30.862 --> 03:33.931
now, would it?

03:33.999 --> 03:36.233
Hey, are you busy?
I'm stuck on something.

03:36.301 --> 03:37.968
I could use
an extra set of eyes.

03:38.036 --> 03:40.771
And I'll let you insert
your own blind joke.

03:40.839 --> 03:43.340
I'd love to,
but I'm on my way out.

03:43.408 --> 03:45.209
I just came to check
a few emails.

03:45.277 --> 03:48.379
I like it.
Banker's hours.

03:48.446 --> 03:49.780
Make that banker's half day.

03:49.848 --> 03:52.116
Hey, you want to grab
a beer later?

03:52.184 --> 03:54.585
I'll try not to smash
a bottle over anyone's head,

03:54.653 --> 03:56.253
but I can't make any promises.

03:56.321 --> 03:58.389
As nice as that sounds,
I'm on my way out of town.

03:58.456 --> 04:01.325
Did Joan put you on an
assignment I don't know about?

04:01.393 --> 04:03.060
I'm taking
a few days vacation.

04:03.128 --> 04:04.395
Really?

04:04.462 --> 04:07.431
This from the woman
who's never taken a day off work

04:07.499 --> 04:09.466
for Thanksgiving, Christmas,
or Kwanzaa.

04:09.534 --> 04:11.869
It was a spontaneous thing.

04:11.937 --> 04:13.837
Now, that is more like
the Annie Walker that I know.

04:13.905 --> 04:15.372
Where you going?

04:15.440 --> 04:16.874
Michael's taking
my sister away,

04:16.942 --> 04:18.608
and they need me
to watch the girls.

04:18.677 --> 04:20.344
What about Michael's parents?
Didn't they just move out there?

04:20.411 --> 04:21.712
They're on a cruise.

04:21.779 --> 04:24.315
And they just now asked
you to come out?

04:24.382 --> 04:25.616
They're not big planners.

04:25.684 --> 04:27.518
Listen, I'm gonna be late
for my flight.

04:27.586 --> 04:31.522
I'm fine, Auggie.
We'll catch up when I get back.

04:47.305 --> 04:50.341
I've never pulled
a job like this in three hours.

04:50.408 --> 04:52.743
I included a rush fee.

04:55.313 --> 04:56.947
This is fully biometric?

04:57.015 --> 04:58.415
I used a blank R.F.I.D. chip

04:58.483 --> 05:01.018
from the actual
Thai facility the GPO uses.

05:01.086 --> 05:03.721
- And she can travel anywhere?
- Any checkpoint in the world.

05:03.788 --> 05:05.222
It routes to a dummy
U.S. government site.

05:05.290 --> 05:06.991
No one here will know
she left the country.

05:07.058 --> 05:08.058
You match the stamps?

05:08.126 --> 05:09.660
And the crease
on the Morocco page

05:09.728 --> 05:11.695
and the coffee stain
on the German stamp.

05:11.763 --> 05:13.430
Trust me--I've done
one or two of these before.

05:13.498 --> 05:14.898
And this needs to be better.

05:14.966 --> 05:17.368
As long as she has
that passport with her,

05:17.435 --> 05:19.603
she'll be fine.
That's all I need to know.

05:22.307 --> 05:27.578
Good luck.

05:44.696 --> 05:46.897
<i>Hola</i> Victor.

05:46.965 --> 05:50.200
<i>¿Como estas?</i>

05:50.268 --> 05:53.704
<i>Gracias.</i>

05:58.443 --> 06:01.178
All that money, and you could
only afford two wheels?

06:01.246 --> 06:03.847
Well, you're welcome
to take a cab if you'd prefer.

06:06.918 --> 06:14.658
♪

06:39.751 --> 06:43.454
Annie, do me a favor--
toss me your passport.

06:43.521 --> 06:46.256
Oh, that's okay.
I can hold on to it.

06:46.324 --> 06:47.691
This isn't America.

06:47.759 --> 06:50.561
You don't leave something
that valuable just lying around.

06:50.628 --> 06:53.697
What's the matter?

06:53.765 --> 06:58.369
You weren't planning
on running away, were you?

06:58.436 --> 06:59.703
Yeah.

06:59.771 --> 07:02.206
I was hoping I'd meet
a strapping young habanero

07:02.273 --> 07:04.475
and start a family down here.

07:04.542 --> 07:08.679
Well, until then,
you'll have to make do with me.

07:29.868 --> 07:32.803
<i>[Can You Save Me?</i>
<i>by Apple Trees and Tangerines]</i>

07:32.871 --> 07:36.871
